SIMPLE: husbandry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Husbandry
<hw>Hus"band*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Care
of domestic affairs; economy; domestic management; thrift.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There's <qex>husbandry</qex> in heaven;⟦br⟧
Their candles are all out.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The business of a husbandman, comprehending the
various branches of agriculture; farming.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Husbandry</qex> supplieth all things necessary for food.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hush</ent>⟦br⟧
